article.description: William & Mary comes back from down 22; beats UNCW 76-72
article.headline: William & Mary comes back from down 22; beats UNCW 76-72
article.linkText: William & Mary comes back from down 22; beats UNCW 76-72
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Marcus Thornton scored 19 points to help William & Mary come back from a 20-point halftime deficit to beat UNC Wilmington 76-72 on Wednesday night. Terry Tarpey hit two free throws with 2:28 left to give the Tribe a 71-70 lead -- its first since it was 9-8 -- after trailing by as many as 22 in the first half. Tarpey made the second free throw of a one-and-one with 25 seconds left to give William & Mary a 74-72 lead. UNCW's Jordon Talley missed a 3-pointer with 14 seconds left and Thornton sealed it with two free throws. Omar Prewitt had 16 and Tarpey added 13 for William & Mary (10-6, 4-1 Colonial Athletic Association). The Tribe started the second half on a 14-4 run. Addison Spruill made 5 of 6 3-pointers and finished with a career-high 33 points for UNC Wilmington (8-8, 3-2). The senior's previous high was 20.
